<tr>
	<td>
		<h2>SPOJ Problem Set (classical)</h2>
				<h1>10509. Cards</h1>
		<h2>Problem code: CRDS</h2>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<p align="justify">
<p>Maricruz have a lot of cards, she always uses her cards to build pyramids as shown<br />in the following image:<br /></p>
<img title="Cards" src="../../content/francky:cards" alt="Cards" />
<p>
A pyramid card of 3 leves.<br />She always wonder how many cards does she need to make a pyramid card of N<br />levels. Your task is to answer that question.<br />Input<br />The first line of the input contains an integer 1<= T <= 1,000. Each of the<br />following T lines will have an integer 1<= N <= 1,000,000.<br />Output<br />For each case, output a single line consisting of the number of cards needed to<br />build a pyramid card of level N modulo 1,000,007.</p>
<p><br />Input Example<br />2</br>
3</br>
7</p>
<p>Output Example<br />15<br />77</p>

